The National Working Committee of the All Progressives Congress has approved new National Officers for the party. The new appointments was confirmed in a statement by the party’s National Publicity Secretary, Lanre Issa-Onilu, on Wednesday. Issa-Onilu said the decision was reached on January 14, 2020 during the meeting of the NWC at the party’s National Secretariat in Abuja. Among the new national officers are the Acting National Secretary, Waziri Bulama; Deputy National Chairman (South), Senator Abiola Ajimobi; and National Auditor, Paul Chukwuma. Issa-Onilu said filling the position of the National Secretary became imperative following the resignation of Mai Mala Buni, who is now the Governor of Yobe State. (The Eagle Online)